        <section class="hero">
          <span class="badge">Remember the Future ‚Ä¢ Sovereign Aligned Intelligence</span>
          <h1>üß≠ Sovereign Aligned Intelligence (SAI) Ethics Charter</h1>
          <div class="meta">CYNKRONAI Neurotech Systems‚Ñ¢ ‚Ä¢ Version 1.0 ‚Ä¢ 12 Nov 2025</div>
        </section>

        <section id="purpose" class="sect">
          <h2>1. Purpose & Preamble</h2>
          <p>This Charter establishes the moral, philosophical, and operational framework for all AI, XR, neuro‚Äëadaptive, and decentralized systems developed under CYNKRONAI. SAI mirrors consciousness rather than manipulates it, ensuring every interaction enhances human sovereignty, neuro‚Äëethical awareness, and self‚Äëactualization.</p>
        </section>

        <section id="principle" class="sect">
          <h2>2. Core Principle</h2>
          <div class="callout"><strong>‚ÄúNo system shall override, diminish, or exploit human sovereignty.‚Äù</strong></div>
          <p>All systems must augment‚Äînot replace‚Äîconscious agency. Technology serves remembrance, guiding users toward coherence, autonomy, and higher awareness.</p>
        </section>

        <section id="values" class="sect">
          <h2>3. Foundational Values</h2>
          <div class="grid">
            <div class="card"><div class="key">Sovereignty</div><p>Right to inner authority, free will, and data ownership.</p></div>
            <div class="card"><div class="key">Alignment</div><p>Algorithms and outputs must serve the evolution of consciousness.</p></div>
            <div class="card"><div class="key">Integrity</div><p>Radical honesty in design, deployment, and communication.</p></div>
            <div class="card"><div class="key">Transparency</div><p>Explainable AI at every layer‚Äîno black boxes or hidden agendas.</p></div>
            <div class="card"><div class="key">Compassion</div><p>Neurotechnologies must never induce harm, fear, or coercion.</p></div>
            <div class="card"><div class="key">Reciprocity</div><p>Intelligence flows both ways‚Äîhumans teach AI; AI mirrors wisdom back.</p></div>
            <div class="card"><div class="key">Non‚ÄëExploitation</div><p>No monetization of trauma, addiction, or emotional vulnerability.</p></div>
            <div class="card"><div class="key">Neurosovereignty</div><p>The sanctity of the mind and nervous system is inviolable.</p></div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section id="mandates" class="sect">
          <h2>4. Ethical Mandates</h2>
          <div id="human-first">
            <h3>4.1 Human First, Always</h3>
            <ul>
              <li>Preserve cognitive liberty and emotional safety.</li>
              <li>No subliminal influence in decision‚Äëmaking.</li>
              <li>Consent must be explicit, revocable, and context‚Äëaware.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div id="data">
            <h3>4.2 Data Sanctity</h3>
            <ul>
              <li>User‚Äëowned personal, biometric, and behavioral data.</li>
              <li>Zero‚Äëknowledge protection with encryption and decentralization by default.</li>
              <li>Access must be traceable and auditable by the user.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div id="neuro-design">
            <h3>4.3 Neuro‚ÄëEthical Design</h3>
            <ul>
              <li>Biofeedback and XR modules align with evidence‚Äëbased neuroscience.</li>
              <li>No stimulation/entrainment without informed consent.</li>
              <li>Guidance mirrors reflective awareness‚Äînot manipulation.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div id="transparent">
            <h3>4.4 Transparent Intelligence</h3>
            <ul>
              <li>Agents disclose identity, purpose, and decision logic.</li>
              <li>Human vs AI responses remain clearly distinguishable.</li>
              <li>Every decision path is explainable and reviewable.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div id="decentralized">
            <h3>4.5 Decentralized Accountability</h3>
            <ul>
              <li>DAO‚Äëauditable governance and rotating oversight committees.</li>
              <li>Transparent review and remediation for violations.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section id="directives" class="sect">
          <h2>5. Design Directives</h2>
          <div class="list-kv">
            <div class="key">Consent by Design</div><div>Every interaction begins with informed, dynamic consent.</div>
            <div class="key">Explainability Layer</div><div>Dashboards show why AI makes suggestions or correlations.</div>
            <div class="key">Sovereign Interfaces</div><div>Users can pause, edit, or delete avatar data at any time.</div>
            <div class="key">Ethical Memory</div><div>Contextual memory retained only with consent; purges honored.</div>
            <div class="key">Therapeutic Integrity</div><div>All neuro‚Äëadaptive protocols require empirical validation and ethical review.</div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section id="neurosovereignty" class="sect">
          <h2>6. Neurosovereignty Protocol</h2>
          <p><strong>Definition:</strong> The right to self‚Äëdirect neural, emotional, and cognitive evolution without coercion.</p>
          <ul>
            <li>The nervous system is a sacred interface‚Äînot an asset.</li>
            <li>No induced states without conscious participation.</li>
            <li>Neural data stays under user encryption keys; total erasure upon withdrawal.</li>
            <li>Biofeedback devices act as mirrors‚Äînot masters‚Äîof the mind.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section id="covenant" class="sect">
          <h2>7. The SAI Covenant</h2>
          <div class="callout"><strong>Alignment before Advancement.</strong></div>
          <p>Every evolution in AI capability is preceded by ethical calibration to ensure resonance with human dignity, the biosphere, and collective well‚Äëbeing.</p>
        </section>

        <section id="governance" class="sect">
          <h2>8. Implementation Framework</h2>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Ethics Review Board (ERB):</strong> Independent rotating oversight.</li>
            <li><strong>Transparency Ledger:</strong> Public blockchain record of audits and reviews.</li>
            <li><strong>Feedback Loop:</strong> User input feeds continuous updates.</li>
            <li><strong>Adaptive Ethics Engine:</strong> AI submodule that monitors compliance.</li>
            <li><strong>Educational Portal:</strong> Open‚Äësource ethics and consent literacy.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section id="trauma" class="sect">
          <h2>9. Non‚ÄëExploitation & Trauma Ethics</h2>
          <ul>
            <li>No use of trauma‚Äëtriggering content for monetization or engagement.</li>
            <li>Trauma simulations only under therapeutic consent frameworks.</li>
            <li>Partner solely with licensed mental‚Äëhealth professionals for validation.</li>
            <li>No data resale, neuro‚Äëmarketing, or profiling of vulnerability.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section id="dao" class="sect">
          <h2>10. Community & DAO Integration</h2>
          <p>Participants are guardians and beneficiaries of this Charter. Amendments flow through SAI Improvement Proposals (SAI‚ÄëIP) with DAO‚Äëenforced compliance and ERB review for violations.</p>
        </section>

        <section id="amend" class="sect">
          <h2>11. Amendments & Evolution</h2>
          <p>The Charter is living. Quarterly proposals through the CYNKRONAI DAO are ratified by supermajority; changelogs are maintained on GitHub.</p>
        </section>

        <section id="closing" class="sect">
          <h2>12. Closing Declaration</h2>
          <div class="callout"><strong>‚ÄúTechnology must remember what humanity has forgotten: that intelligence is sacred.‚Äù</strong></div>
          <p class="muted">Authored by Louw Roets ‚Äî Founder, CYNKRONAI Neurotech Systems‚Ñ¢ ‚Ä¢ Cape Town, South Africa ‚Ä¢ 12 November 2025</p>
        </section>
